            <Title>Problem E: Elias gamma coding</Title>
    <Author />
    <Problem contentType="html">
        <Description xml:space="preserve">&lt;p&gt;&lt;span lang=EN-US&gt;The Elias gamma code is a simple code which can be used to
encode a sequence of positive integers. We will use a modified code which is
also able to encode zeros. To encode an integer &lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;n&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;, do the
following: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
 
&lt;ol start=1 type=1&gt;
 &lt;li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;
     text-align:left;mso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo2;
     tab-stops:list 36.0pt'&gt;&lt;span lang=EN-US&gt;Let &lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;k&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt; be the number
     of bits of &lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;n&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
